  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "If you had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, what would you do?",
  "response": "If I had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, I would focus on a combination of personal fulfillment, making a positive impact on the world, and ensuring my legacy. Here's a potential plan:\n\n1. **Personal Fulfillment (10% of the budget - $300 million):**\n   - **Travel:** I would spend time traveling to places I've always wanted to visit, experiencing different cultures, and enjoying the world's natural wonders. This would include luxury accommodations and unique experiences ($100 million).\n   - **Hobbies and Passions:** I would invest in pursuing my passions, such as art, music, or sports, including learning new skills or supporting projects related to these interests ($100 million).\n   - **Family and Friends:** I would ensure that my loved ones are taken care of, perhaps by setting up trusts or gifting them experiences and memories to share together ($100 million).\n\n2. **Philanthropy and Impact (80% of the budget - $2.4 billion):**\n   - **Health and Medical Research:** I would fund research into diseases that are currently incurable or difficult to treat, with the aim of advancing medical science and potentially helping others live longer, healthier lives ($1 billion).\n   - **Education:** I would establish scholarships and educational programs to help underprivileged individuals access quality education and opportunities for personal growth ($500 million).\n   - **Environmental Conservation:** I would support initiatives focused on protecting endangered species, preserving natural habitats, and combating climate change ($500 million).\n   - **Social Justice and Equality:** I would fund organizations working to promote equality, fight discrimination, and support marginalized communities ($400 million).\n\n3. **Legacy Projects (10% of the budget - $300 million):**\n   - **Foundation:** I would establish a foundation to manage my philanthropic efforts, ensuring that they continue beyond my lifetime and have a lasting impact ($200 million).\n   - **Memorial Projects:** I would fund the creation of public spaces, such as parks or museums, that reflect my values and provide enjoyment and education for future generations ($100 million).\n\nIn the remaining time, I would focus on enjoying life to the fullest, making the most of each day, and being present with the people I love. By balancing personal enjoyment with meaningful contributions to the world, I believe I could live a fulfilling and impactful final three years.",
